Tables of DGL points

Last update: 2024-05-29 09:08:46

Experimental observations

  • smallCM + conj is always 1: smallCM points are always defined over Qp
  • smallCM + triv is 1 when D = 1 (mod 8)
  • smallRM + triv is 1 when D = 0 (mod 4)
  • smallRM + triv is very often defined over Q(i), but we have some exceptions!

Recovering data

  • For "triv": Cp.<t> = Qq(p**2, prec); J = Cp(2*J0)
  • For "conj": Cp.<t> = Qq(p**2, prec); a = Cp(J0); t0 = t - t.trace()/2; b = ((1-a**2)/t0.norm()).sqrt(); J = a + b * t0

Summary

  • Total completely trivial: 1230 (simultaneously for both characters)
  • Total unrecognized: 1448
  • Total recognized (nontrivial): 682
  • Total rows: 4218

Column description

  • p : prime
  • D : absolute value of discriminant
  • type : either smallCM or smallRM
  • char : "triv" means J·J' and "conj" means J/J'
  • recognized : whether the point has been recognized as algebraic
  • field : polynomial defining the field HJ generated by Jtriv or Jconj
  • factor : a representation for the factorization of the ideal (Jtriv) or (Jconj). Only the prime below each prime in HJ is written. The list gives the primes in the support. Primes = 3 (mod 4) are represented in blue, while those = 1 (mod 4) are represented in red. The symbols (a) and (l) indicate which recognition algorithm was used.
  • poly : minimal polynomial of ζ·Jtriv or ζ·Jconj for a certain root of unity ζ
  • hpoly : polynomial defining the compositum of Q(i) with the Hilbert class field of real/imaginary field of absolute discriminant D.
  • o(ζ) : order of ζ
  • J : an integer-encoded form for Jtriv or Jconj. See above for how to recover it
